        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 1:52PM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 152 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Henderson, moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Henderson, Hallsville, Tatum, New London, Lakeport, Easton, Chalk
Hill, Stewart, Monroe and Oak Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
